title.narrative: (901.1) CHILDREN'S RIGHT TO HEALTH ANDWELL BEING

description.narrative: Children's Right to Health and Well being - Families, particularly the most disadvantaged and vulnerable, supported to access quality health basic services and provide nurturing care to infants and young children in a safe and stimulating home environment., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Critical bottlenecks for affordable health care, child survival and young child well being are removed

description.narrative: During the year, support was focused on rolling out of COVID-19 vaccines, by coordinating with relevant regional partners, providing technical guidance and support to countries, facilitating vaccines procurement and creation of demand for immunization. The program continued to support countries in maintaining and restoring essential services, including routine immunization to reach those children who missed vaccinations. Support to Nutrition program was focused on enhancing the policy and system capacities for prevention of childhood obesity during the first and the second decade of life as well as prevention of micronutrient deficiencies such as Iodine, Iron and etc among children and women. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/02/2022
